description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Neurodevelopmental (Community) Paediatrician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10 PAs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent Post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Epsom &amp; St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit a Consultant Neurodevelopmental (Community) Paediatrician to help deliver our service in the north of Surrey. The post will be based at Epsom General Hospital. While the main base for this post will be Epsom Hospital, the post holder may be required to work at other sites as required. Epsom Hospital has an integrated paediatric service with acute and community paediatrics on the same site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neurodevelopmental / Community Paediatrics Service treats children with a range of clinical presentations which include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developmental Paediatrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Neurodevelopmental disorders including Autism Spectrum Disorders (ASD) and ADHD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational Paediatrics (SEN)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Children in the care of the Local Authority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Neurodisability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will play a crucial role in ensuring the team continues to deliver a high quality community paediatrics service and will be involved in strategic planning of services with our local partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Consultant Paediatrician will deliver community paediatric clinics including neurodevelopmental and neurobehavioural clinics. Amongst other skills, the post holder will be able to assess and manage children with ASD and ADHD. They will be able to provide medical reports in support of EHCP applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are expected to be on the GMC specialist register or be within 6 months of obtaining CCT at the time of interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Stephanie Kirk and Tim Marr &lt;br /&gt;Job title Consultant Paediatrician and Clinical Lead &lt;br /&gt;Email address stephanie.kirk1@nhs.net &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Tim Marr - t.marr@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
